-->PROJECT TITLE: 
PLASTICS TYPES PROPERTIES ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES
-->DESCRIPTION:

Plastics: Types, Properties, and Environmental Issues is an educational project developed to increase awareness about plastics, 
their characteristics, and their impact on the environment.
The project provides detailed information about different types of plastics, including their properties, applications, recycling methods, 
and environmental challenges such as pollution, waste accumulation, and harm to ecosystems.
The project is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create an interactive and user-friendly interface,
while Python is used to organize and display information efficiently. 
The aim is to educate users about responsible plastic usage, proper waste management, recycling practices, 
and sustainable alternatives, encouraging environmentally conscious decision-making.

-->PROBLEM STATEMENT:

Plastic is widely used in everyday life because of its durability, versatility, and low cost. 
However, many people lack awareness of the different types of plastics, their properties, recycling codes, 
and environmental impacts. Improper disposal and excessive use of plastics contribute to pollution, harm wildlife and marine ecosystems,
and create long-term environmental challenges.
There is a need for accessible educational resources that help people understand plastics and their environmental effects.

-->SOLUTION STATEMENT:

To address this problem, this project provides an interactive educational platform.
That explains the types of plastics, their properties, uses, recycling methods, and environmental issues.
Built using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Python, the platform presents information in a simple and engaging way,
Helping users improve their understanding of plastics and encouraging responsible usage, recycling, and sustainable waste management.

